'''Omar Rekik''' ({{langx|ar|عمر رقيق }}; born 20 December 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Slovenian PrvaLiga]] club [[NK Maribor|Maribor]].<ref>{{Soccerway|id=omar-rekik/549221|accessdate=}}</ref> Born in the Netherlands, he represents the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

== Early life ==
Born in [[Helmond]], Netherlands<ref name=":3" /> to a Tunisian father and a Dutch mother,<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|last=Jerbi|first=Rania|date=27 May 2021|title=Equipe nationale –Tunisie: Omar Rekik officiellement " Aigle de Carthage "|url=https://africafootunited.com/equipe-nationale-tunisie-omar-rekik-officiellement-aigle-de-carthage/|access-date=16 June 2021|website=Africa Foot United|language=fr-FR|archive-date=12 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210612225042/https://africafootunited.com/equipe-nationale-tunisie-omar-rekik-officiellement-aigle-de-carthage/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Jerbi|first=Rania|date=31 May 2021|title=Tunisie: Karim Rekik sur les traces de son frère Omar ?|url=https://africafootunited.com/tunisie-karim-rekik-sur-les-traces-de-son-frere-omar/|access-date=15 June 2021|website=Africa Foot United|language=fr-FR|archive-date=23 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623092749/https://africafootunited.com/tunisie-karim-rekik-sur-les-traces-de-son-frere-omar/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Rekik was part of several big European clubs during his youth career, following his brother [[Karim Rekik|Karim]] from [[Feyenoord]] to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], then [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] and [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], before joining [[Hertha BSC|Hertha Berlin]] in 2017.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|date=18 October 2018|title=Omar Rekik: talento tunisino classe 2001|url=https://www.worldfootballscouting.com/scheda-giocatore/omar-rekik-talento-tunisino-classe-2001/|access-date=15 June 2021|website=World Football Scouting|language=it-IT}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Rault|first=Mathieu|date=19 November 2020|title=Arsenal veut l'ancien Marseillais Omar Rekik|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a9202567754292505247-arsenal-veut-lancien-marseillais-omar-rekik|access-date=15 June 2021|website=Foot Mercato|language=fr}}</ref> However, their careers eventually split during the [[2020–21 Hertha BSC season|2020–21 season]], as Omar was transferred from the [[Bundesliga]] side to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in January 2021,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Omar Rekik signs professional contract|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/omar-rekik-signs-professional-contract|access-date=15 June 2021|website=Arsenal F.C.}}</ref><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|date=7 January 2021|title=Arsenal sign Omar Rekik|url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/arsenal-sign-omar-rekik-936923|access-date=15 June 2021|website=BeSoccer}}</ref> while Karim joined Spanish side [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] a few months earlier.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

== Club career==
On 31 January 2023, Rekik joined [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] in the [[EFL Championship]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|website=Sparta Rotterdam|url=https://www.sparta-rotterdam.nl/sparta-huurt-omar-rekik-arsenal/|title=Sparta huurt Omar Rekik van Arsenal|date=20 June 2022|access-date=20 July 2022|language=nl}}</ref> On 1 September 2023, he re-joined Wigan Athletic in [[EFL League One]] on a short-term loan deal until January 2024.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Arsenal|url=https://www.arsenal.com/omar-rekik-joins-wigan-athletic-loan-league-one-deal/|title=Omar Rekik joins Wigan Athletic on loan|date=1 September 2023|access-date=2 September 2023|website=Arsenal F.C.}}</ref>

On 2 February 2024, Rekik moved on a new loan to [[Servette FC|Servette]] in Switzerland, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|website=Servette FC|url=https://servettefc.ch/omar-rekik-rejoint-les-grenat/|title=Omar Rekik rejoint les Grenat|trans-title=Omar Rekik joins The Garnets|date=2 February 2024|access-date=3 February 2024|language=fr}}</ref>

== International career ==
While his brother [[Karim Rekik|Karim]] was already capped for the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]], Omar was first selected in the [[Tunisian Football Federation|Tunisia]] under-21 selection in October 2018, aged just 16,<ref name=":3" /> before joining the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands under-18]] a month later.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Elfrink|first=Rik|date=15 November 2018|title=KNVB maakt werk van Omar Rekik, die bij Oranje onder 18 in de basis staat|url=https://www.ed.nl/psv/knvb-maakt-werk-van-omar-rekik-die-bij-oranje-onder-18-in-de-basis-staat~a979f3f4/|journal=[[Eindhovens Dagblad]]}}</ref>

Rekik eventually decided to join the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]] in May 2021, as he was selected by [[Mondher Kebaier]] along with other young players such as [[Hannibal Mejbri]].<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=30 May 2021|title=Cérémonie de présentation des deux néo-internationaux, Hannibal Mejbri et Omar Rekik|url=https://www.mosaiquefm.net/fr/video/602996/ceremonie-de-presentation-des-deux-neo-internationaux-hannibal-mejbri-et-omar-rekik|access-date=16 June 2021|website=[[Mosaïque FM]]|language=fr}}</ref> He made his international senior debut on 15 June 2021, starting as a midfielder in a 1–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] win against [[Mali national football team|Mali]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 June 2021|title=Amical: Formation rentrante de la Tunisie face au Mali|url=https://www.kawarji.com/actu-66449-amical-formation-rentrante-de-la-tunisie-face-au-mali.html|access-date=15 June 2021|website=kawarji.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 June 2021|title=Amical, Tunisie –Mali : La victoire et c'est tout pour les Aigles de Carthage {{!}} Africa Foot United|url=https://africafootunited.com/amical-tunisie-mali-la-victoire-et-cest-tout-pour-les-aigles-de-carthage/|access-date=15 June 2021|website=africafootunited.com|language=fr-FR|archive-date=1 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210801141842/https://africafootunited.com/amical-tunisie-mali-la-victoire-et-cest-tout-pour-les-aigles-de-carthage/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

